  "prompt": "Does money laundering fall under criminal legislation?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is a criminal offense in most countries and is covered under criminal legislation. It typically involves:\n\n1. Concealing the origins of illegally obtained money\n2. Transforming \"dirty\" money into seemingly \"clean\" funds\n3. Making illegally obtained money appear legitimate\n\nMoney laundering is considered a serious financial crime and is often prosecuted under:\n- Criminal codes\n- Anti-money laundering (AML) laws\n- Financial regulatory statutes\n\nPenalties can include:\n- Significant fines\n- Imprisonment\n- Asset seizure\n- Criminal record\n\nMany countries have specific laws and regulatory frameworks designed to prevent and prosecute money laundering activities.",
